content:
We know it's far from simple to manage group plans for your employees. That's why we've created Group Voluntary Benefits Application to simplify how you manage plans and enroll employees.

With all the numerous coverages and attributes in group plans, you probably want to try multiple combinations before you create a plan that works best for your organization and employees. To help you, we've created some example workflows in Group Voluntary Benefits Application that help you arrive at your ideal plan that much faster.

You can:

Create a quote: Quickly and efficiently configure, reprice, and view a quote for group plans.
Create a contract: Your contract in PDF or MS Word format is just one click away.
Enroll members: Upload group benefits product enrollment data with census members and dependents by using the Enrollment Census Lightning web component.
Enroll a new hire: Enroll new hires in the middle of a contract term.
Terminate a group member: Cancel the policy and update the term premium for a group member and their dependents.

Your org comes with a Digital Policyholder Portal that serves as a self-service tool for policyholders to enroll in plans, update their account information, and see details of all their policies.

This includes:

Policyholder Digital Experience Site
Group Benefits Broker Digital Experience Site

Before using the Group Voluntary Benefits Application, you need to complete some configuration tasks. This section walks you through all the post-deployment steps that you must complete.

The Group Voluntary Benefits Application is built with a product model that includes:

Group Voluntary Benefits Product Model
Group Voluntary Benefits Expression Sets

You can also use the following business processes:

Quote Business Process For Group Voluntary Benefits
Contract Business Process
Group Enrollment Business Process
Mid-Term Adjustment Business Process
title: Simplifying Group Voluntary Benefits Management with OmniStudio
